text:
Super value for money Hot Bur Bur Cha Cha ($2.80) that comes with Gula Melaka and a generous serving of bouncy chewy colourful sticky jellies. Do note they sell hot bur bur cha cha only on Fridays!

The Tang Yuan ($2.50 glutinous rice balls) are also well done, swimming in a hot bowl of dried longan sweet soup.

They are closed on Mondays. And opens till 7pm.
Loved their tou Suan and bubur terigu. Stall owner is very friendly and the tou suan sold out very early.

Old school dessert stall
Lady is friendly
Love their barley gingko
